caption: The flavors here are amazing. Get a seat in the courtyard!

The diamond in the rough! 10 out of 10 out of 10 stars. We stopped in for a very quick drink and small bite, almost left because of seating availability, but OMG So thankful we didn't. This food is ... amazing!! The bread and butter combo tastes like vanilla custard, the filet medallions melted in my mouth and even made my picky teenager happy, and the wine selection is impeccable!!!! Please stop here if you come to New Orleans!!
We loved everything about this place. The staff, the food, the heat lamp on every table outside! Fantastic!

My fav place for quality quality meals. Got there about three, it wasn't crowded. Service is typically great. The place has a cool feel to it.
Service was the best and food was amazing! My gf and i had to go back for seconds. Cant wait to try it again.
Absolutely delicious
One of my most favorite places in New Orleans.
Food is really good. New Orleans has lots of good food but this was better than anything we had in town. The service was friendly and attentive.
quality meals, mmm, so delicious. super place to meet and chat with coworkers. looking forward to a return trip. it has a cool atmosphere. they have a lot of positive reviews for a reason.

My sister in law and I had the BEST time at Oleans Grapevine W&B!!! The atmosphere is wonderful, especially being smack dab in the quarter. We had an amazing server, and the food and wine was *chef kiss* devine! This will be my go to place in NOLA as it is hands down my favorite!
Definitely one of the highlights of our trip to NOLA! The food and the service were both excellent. Mark was very friendly and answered any questions we had. I do recommend

Great food
Best meal I had in the French Quarter. The mussels. I'm serious.... the mussels.

Great food, atmosphere and service

Amazing happy hour, drinks are great. Staff is amazing. All the bacon you can eat at happy hour.  Dinners are amazing. Prices are good. Best find in New Orleans.

LOVE! We come here all the time for their happy hour at 4PM-6PM and after 10PM. They have the most incredible cheese boards and wine specials! They also give you free bacon during happy hour!!! My favorite salad is the Baby Spinach.

Like most places in NOLA, I loved it!

Good was great, service was great. Hidden gem for sure.
Excellent food and service.  A must try while visiting new Orleans.  The rack of lamb was amazing.  Not to be missed

We visit each time we come to NOLA. If you are looking for excellent NOLA cusine off Burbon St. without the tourist trap nonsense, you can't go wrong.  Locals dine here so come before your French quarter dubautchery so you don't make a fool of yourself.  The bbq shrimp appetizer is very traditional NOLA style and well prepared to make it easy to eat without a lot of work.  All food with the exception of the ice cream is made in-house.  Grapevine is food lover's paradise, and the seafood dishes are top notch.  Food 5, service 4, prices 3.
All of us were happy with our dining experience. Door and service was good.
Amazing restaurant.  We sat outside in the garden.  Great wine choices

We asked for a place that locals visit and we were very glad that we did. The outdoor courtyard has umbrellas with heaters and lots of plants that make it comfortable in almost any weather. The service was prompt and personable, the food among the best we have had in NOLA, and prices quite reasonable. Very highly recommended.
I love this place, they have a beautiful garden where you can ait outside !
Good Food! Friendly atmosphere! The Owners are Awesome! God Bless this Establishment!!
Great food & drink! Very attentive staff and a very nice atmosphere.
The food is fantastic and the atmosphere was not to be beat.   A great selection of lighter and heavier fare, we had a group of 10 and everyone found something they loved.

Bacon happy hour doesn't mean a few pieces of thin bacon, it means thick BASKETS full of bacon. This joint is very reasonably priced for happy hour. They do stock a full bar as well, if wine is not your drink of choice. Great ambiance and atmosphere, overall feel is cozy and relaxed. Service can get a little slow as the crowds pick up.
Crab and corn soup was delicious. Relaxed atmosphere.
Had the cauliflower and gorgonzola soup. Delicious!  and their mussels are really good. Amazing wine and service. Go for the bacon happy hour if you can

Went with friends on another friend’s recommendation. Grapevine did not disappoint - great food (cheese plate, baked Brie, goat cheese salad), atmosphere (courtyard), and service (Sarah).  We will be going again next time in NOLA.
It's what new orleans used to be but at a five star level. Great food and a comfortable feeling of old world ambiance. Courtyard is tight and charming.
We loved it......

Lovely place. You can either sit in the courtyard  or inside with a bar/tavern setting. Food was great, portions were generous too. To top it off, this place is also a wine bar.  Overall a nice choice: good quality, not too crowded.

We also tried the baked brie with garlic cream sauce, which was very good. We will definitely be back next time we are in the city!

Good food and service thou we couldn't sit outside  thou there were empty tables
I went to this place three years ago and came back this past month. Considering we are a very foodie family it takes a lot for me to visit the same place twice.... Sold.

Only stayed two days in New Orleans and the Grapevine Wine Bar & Bistro was across the street from the Bourbon Orleans Hotel where my family and I were staying.  Obviously, we checked to see if the reviews were good.  After all, if you have a bad meal in New Orleans - it's your own dang fault.  I decided to have a salad, appetizer and a dessert.  The Duck Breast Salad was perfectly prepared and really tasty.  I was hoping it would be a good pairing with the Pinot Noir flight of wines that my wife ordered.  And it was.  The appetizer I went with was the New Orleans Barbeque Shrimp.  Again, I was really blown away with the flavors and the bread served for dipping and to cut the acidity of the barbeque sauce was really good.  I have to say the highlight of the meal was the French Vanilla & White Chocolate Bread Pudding.  I kid you not, this might be one of the best desserts I have had in years.  Going to Orleans Grapevine Wine Bar & Bistro made the rest of the places in the French Quarter a tough comparison.
Good wine choices. Great food.

Simply Amazing, we were recommended to go her by another couple and I was thoroughly impressed. Very classy place with music a lot of great wine and  very laid back. I had Seafood Gumbo Crab cakes and my Wife had the Mussels everything was delectable and the presentation immaculate.

Main part of dish was "good" but supporting stuff, such as veg, potatoes etc was very bad . The lamb dish was a confusion. The lamb itself was nicely cooked, but herb encrusted?? No way. Not impressed at all. Had much better food and service elsewhere.

I suppose it's fine if you like pricey food with tastes that don't make sense. I ordered the scallops with rice. Never again. The rice was sweet and juicy because they put some sort of blueberry reduction mop water all over it. The bbq shrimp was so obviously pre frozen..the sauce they drowned that in couldn't mask the lack of effort unfortunately. The waitress was nice enough and the free warm french bread was the best part. But the butter was sweet and lackluster as well. Wasn't a great first night dining experience..I prayed the rest of new Orleans wasn't like this. Go to FRENCH TOAST!
Had dinner and cocktails with 3 other friends, dinner was great.
Absolute MUST when in New Orleans. Happy hour to die for with that basket of bacon to nibble on ❤️

Loved the server I had Jason was super cool
Awesome place we happened upon. Excellent food and wines. Courtyard.

Please follow us on Facebook and Instagram at SNDTravels. First trip to the French Quarter and looking forward to great food. Having looked at reviews of several places we chose here because of the menu. Sitting outside in the courtyard, we were looking forward to a great experience. Our server seemed to be the only person there that was disinterested in being at work or answering menu questions. Everyone else seemed to be friendly. They brought out bread and butter to start which was fresh and hot. While neither of us are raw oyster eaters I have found fried oysters good on occasion but Diane never has been a fan so for some reason we ordered the Oysters Orleans, oyster cooked with asiago cheese and bacon. Feeling adventurous I guess. What a great choice. We wished we had ordered a full order instead of half. Diane then had the scallops small plate with mushroom wild rice and blackberry brandy reduction. The scallops were few but very good but the rice had a bit to much reduction sauce and was to runny. I had the Gulf Fish almandine made with drum. It just didn't work. The vegies were good but the fish was bland and the almandine sauce was just butter and almonds. Far from the quality I paid for. Half good half disappointing. I wanted to like it but I would definitely try someplace new next time.

Nice selection of wine. We enjoyed a salad and cheese board. The cheese board had a nice selection of cheeses with some nice supporting characters like apple slices, strawberries and grapes. Please give me a like if you find this review helpful.
Excellent in everyway
Food was average. Service was terrible. Restaurant was not busy. We didn’t request anything off menu. All food fir each guest per course was not delivered together.
Great atmosphere, great service, and yummy food.  We really enjoyed the wine flights as well.  Bacon happy hour is fun touch.

Honestly, one of the best dining experiences I've had! Amazing food, great drinks, and a very friendly staff. The food here is a little pricey, but in my opinion its totally worth it. Make sure to go during happy hour, and try a few different wine choices!

(Translated by Google) Very pleasant, it's nice to find a little Europe in its plate with vegetables and spices! And the patio is very nice.  (Original) Très plaisant, ça fait plaisir de retrouver un peu d'Europe dans son assiette avec des légumes et des épices ! Et le patio est très agréable.

Extensive wine selection, great food and friendly staff.  Bacon happy hour at 4 and 10 everyday!
Wonderful food, atmosphere and service. Definitely coming back!
Loved this place
The vegetarian options were terrible. Just a huge plate of random vegetables without any seasoning or sauce.

We had the shrimp appetizer, followed by the tenderloin and lamb chops. Everything was excellent, service was exceptional, and the atmosphere out back was great. I would highly suggest this to anyone traveling to new orleans. Also, the creme brulee was perfect to top the whole thing off.
The food is absolutely delicious! Their pork chops was perfectly grilled en their fillet steak melted in your mouth! Would definitely recommend this place !
I had the Crawfish and crab cakes. Great service, tasty food and a fun vibe.
The food is amazing! Best Rack of Lamb ever!

Great food great service. Try the bbq shrimp and compliment the chef!

While in the Quarter celebrating my birthday, I came here on the recommendation of a security guard at a nearby bar. It was delightful. Awesome courtyard, great wine selection and cheese plates, good food in the heart of the French Quarter.

I always love ending my night at this quaint restaurant. They have happy hour twice a day. The vest one is from 10pm-Midnight. Why? BACON! They give you bacon during happy hour! The food is good, the desserts are great, and the bar drinks are consistent. They have a patio if you like dining outside and there are fans to cool things a bit. The wine selection is good (not fancy, ok) they offer flights.

I walked in and sat at the bar. When they asked if I wanted a food menu I said only a drink for now. Gradually the nice vibe won me over. I ordered catch of the day. I got to talking to someone and we had a great time. Then another person came in and she was interesting too. Good place.
Kinda expensive as the portion size is pretty less.
Such a lovely restaurant. Great atmosphere. Great service. I highly recommend.

I am a celiac and visited this restaurant because of its variety of gluten free options. When we were seated I informed our waiter of my allergy and he told me to order meals with the small asterisk because they are gluten free. Let me start off by saying the selection is awesome and there are gluten free options in every category. I ordered the BBQ shrimp and asked the waiter to make sure the French bread is on the side. When the BBQ shrimp arrived the bowl was filled with tasty shrimp and FRENCH BREAD. I informed the waiter that they accidentally put bread in my shrimp and his response was "are you so allergic that you can't eat it?" I felt like I was being asked to take a light poisoning. I took the precaution of photographing my order prior to sending it back. Our main courses arrived a few minutes later and the waiter asked if I still wanted my BBQ shrimp. I said yes and they brought it right out. Trouble is they pulled the bread out and sent me the same shrimp. I told the waiter I didn't want it and explained that it was the same order and it would be poison for me. He then said they made it fresh for me and that it was a newly prepared order. I then showed him the photographs and he took it back. I then  went to the bathroom and my waiter walked in. We both felt a little awkward due to the attempted poisoning. It really must have bothered my waiter because he used the urinal and walked straight out without washing his hands!!! Little did I know but gluten was the least of my worries as urine was also on the menu. My double cut pork chop was delicious and well prepared. The fish Amandine was also amazing and the wine was amazing. With some gluten sensitivity training and some basic hygiene training this place will be a TEN but until the staff has a sign reminding them to wash hands before returning to work we are all at risk.
Excellent staff and food, will return
Great place eat at the bar and for sunshine!  She is great!
Amazing time we dined at the "Special Table" for a 7 course meal big thanks to Kelly Our server and Mark the General Manager for an great Anniversary dinner

Excellent creol food, nice location, friendly staff and great winelist. Just make sure, when you're not in a hurry, not to order everything right away. Because the kitchen is SUPERFAST!!!! Overall a great restaurant

Seemed like kind of a hole in the wall, just off Bourbon Street (Was also Sunday night). Good selection of wine. They gave complimentary Bacon (very tasty) , which should be a thing everywhere! Bartender was a super nice guy. Offered great service.
Had a Caeser Salad and the pan seared sea scallops. Both were excellent. No beers on tap, only bottled.

Absolutely one of the best meals we’ve ever had. We had the warm Brie, rack of lamb (incredible) with truffle mashed potatoes and the double cut pork chop with pancetta and sweet potato hash. Service was fantastic too, we were greeted by a very nice woman who sat us quickly and our server Kelly was so sweet! Our entrees were brought out so quickly yet were so fresh.  Highly recommend!!!

Service, food and ambiance...all fantastic!  Highly recommended.  Rack of lamb melts in your mouth,  Lobster was huge and cooked perfectly.  Completely stuffed, we still had ti have the pecan pie...Best we've ever had,  rich, but not iver the top sweet,  delicious! Enjoy

Happy Hour in NOLA is perfect time to visit the Grapevine. Great find just off Bourbon Street. Nice menu selection of appetizers and entrees. We had the shrimp and scallops special, rack of lamb and steak au poivre. All delicious including the goat cheese cheesecake and vanilla bread pudding.

This was the highlight of our trip. Incredible staff made us feel right at home. A large selection of brilliant cocktails paired with the best meal we had the entire trip. The outdoor patio was really comfortable. Love this place.

Everything was amazing. They let our small, well behaved pup join us in the courtyard. Our waitress was wonderful and the food was divine. My hubby and I each ordered wine flights and we shared the baked brie, Angus medallions, as well as the mushroom de vin. Thanks for a great time, Grapevine!

Great food, service, atmosphere and wine!  Quaint courtyard to have dinner. Bartenders very friendly and service was great!  Highly recommend!  A little peaceful oasis amid the craziness of Bourbon St.

Also had a bread pudding for dessert which turned out to be too much for 2 people to share. Would love to eat here again.

Amazing food.. gluten free options delicious... If you can sit outside do it very quaint. I had catch of the day and it was one of the best fish dishes I have had.  It was grouper topped with lump crab and claw crab. So Yummy.. Highly recommend

Great patio very peaceful (i'm putting a star on it), but service and food were a total disaster, for a quite high price.  Had a fish and a steak, were not seasoning, oily, uncooked for the meat, overcooked for the fish... Very bad experience.  waiters looked quite unhappy and not helpful at all.  After having paid an over 100$ bill (diner for 2 of us, sharing an appetizer and without any desert), i went immediately eat somewhere else a random streetfood kebab on Bourbon street wich was much better. What a shame...  if you are searching for good food at reasonable price, run away !
The food was incredible! Highly recommend the escargot and the mushroom du vin.

Excellent and intimate place, great drinks and the attention of the staff (specially Emma) was amazing they made room for us and we had a great time.

We went to Grapevine last night while in town for a cruise. We met the Wonderful owners at the door. We were seated and served by Carrie. Everyone in our party had an amazing food. Carrie was attentive to our needs and offered great suggestions. I'm sure this will be our finest meal of the week!
Great New Orleans vibe.  Great food. Met the owner Pam who came to introduce herself and bought us dessert. Great last meal in New Orleans.

Orleans Grapevine has a nice atmosphere and great service! We went on a Saturday during Happy Hour. My friend and I had to wait for a few minutes to be greeted but were taken to a table right away and told about the specials. I believe they told us that they didn’t serve the full menu until around 6pm but that we were able to get drinks and appetizers. A huge plus for me is that they serve free bacon during happy hour. Who does that?!? They also serve warm baguettes with a spicy butter for the table to share. We both enjoyed the Pecans Praline drink. It was very sweet and something that I’d never tried before. I will absolutely stop by this gem the next time I’m in New Orleans.

I have been to this restaurant at least 10 times over the past 4 years.  Food is great.  There is a problem with the service the last few trips.  I let it go because it could have been a bad day.  Now, it is a pattern. Was there a change in ownership?  I had a 30 minute wait for an appetizer and it was not busy. No reason given why it was so late and not hot.  Server knew nothing about wine. The last trip, the server forgot to enter the order.  Then, brought the wrong food to our table. Three years ago we had one of the best servers in my life, the guy must have worked at Commanders. The food was great and we decided to keep coming back.  I will give it a few years to see if they can work out their issues. Hopefully, the kitchen staff stays.

Not very impressed with the service at this restaurant. Went in to meet my family (a 10 top), could not stay as we had just driven for 6 hours with 2 toddlers. Asked if I could order something to go, waitress said yes, but ordering at the bar would be quicker. Went to the bar and bartender stated that they did not take to go orders at the restaurant. I said the waitress told me to order at the bar it would be faster. He made a show like he would check with the chef and the chef said no. Not sure what is different from preparing food to serve in the restaurant versus food to go. Could have just made me a regular plate and I could have boxed it myself. Guess they don't need business or good customer opinions. The rest of the family had already ordered or we would have all just walked out. So much for good old south Louisiana hospitality.

Monday, about 6:30pm, party of 4. We asked for seating in the courtyard. A young man said he would check availability. He returned quickly with 4 menus and gestured for us to follow. Immediately, the female at the hostess station stopped him and made this comment: "Oh, no...we can't seat them." Then, looking at us, said: "We only have one table for 5 available. We have to keep it open for a party of FIVE." Needless to say, we left, but I managed to say, "What a great business decision!"  I hope the owner sees this comment. 2 of us are locals. We always bring our visiting friends to a variety of city restaurants. This one will never get any of our, or our friends business. Word of mouth marketing...
